<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>you should talk • you shouldn’t talk</xh5><p> <i>you should talk</i>—(also: you can talk) you are in no position to criticize because you are at least as guilty as the person you are criticizing <i>(used as an ironic or sarcastic response to a person who has just spoken): </i>“You are cold-hearted.” “<u>You should talk</u> of all people!”</p><p> <i>you shouldn’t talk</i>—(also: you can’t talk) = you should talk: “Andy’s always late. He won’t be here in time for dinner.” “<u>You shouldn’t talk</u>. You haven’t been on time for dinner for years.”</p> </entry>
